<h1>MicroJava Compiler</h1>

<p>
This project represents an implementation of a <b>MicroJava compiler</b>.
</p>

<p>
The compiler is implemented in Java and consists of the following components:
</p>

<ul>
    <li><b>Lexical Analyzer</b> (JFlex)</li>
    <li><b>Syntax Analyzer</b> (Java CUP)</li>
    <li><b>Semantic Analyzer</b></li>
    <li><b>Code Generator</b> for the MicroJava virtual machine</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Supported Language Features</h2>

<p>The compiler supports the following MicroJava language constructs:</p>

<ul>
<li><b>Basic constructs</b>
    <ul>
        <li>Global constants, variables and enumerations</li>
        <li>Local variables</li>
        <li>Functions and the <code>main</code> function</li>
    </ul>
</li>

<li><b>Expressions</b>
    <ul>
        <li>Arithmetic expressions (+, -, *, /, %)</li>
        <li>Unary minus</li>
        <li>Relational operators</li>
        <li>Ternary operator (<code>? :</code>)</li>
    </ul>
</li>

<li><b>Arrays</b>
    <ul>
        <li>Creation of arrays (<code>new Type[Expr]</code>)</li>
        <li>Array indexing</li>
        <li><code>length</code> and Built-in <code>len</code> property</li>
    </ul>
</li>

<li><b>Statements</b>
    <ul>
        <li>Assignment</li>
        <li>Increment / decrement</li>
        <li>Function calls</li>
        <li><code>read</code> and <code>print</code></li>
    </ul>
</li>

<li><b>Control flow</b>
    <ul>
        <li><code>if / else</code></li>
        <li><code>for</code> loops</li>
        <li><code>switch</code> statements</li>
        <li><code>break</code> and <code>continue</code></li>
        <li><code>return</code></li>
    </ul>
</li>

</ul>

