<h2>Lexical Analyzer</h2>

<p>
The <b>lexical analyzer</b> is implemented using <b>JFlex</b>.  
Its role is to read a MicroJava source file and convert the input character stream into a sequence of tokens.
</p>

<p>
The lexer specification is located in:
</p>

<pre>spec/mjlexer.lex</pre>

<p>
The lexer recognizes the following categories of tokens:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Keywords (<code>program</code>, <code>if</code>, <code>for</code>, <code>switch</code>, etc.)</li>
<li>Identifiers</li>
<li>Integer, character and boolean constants</li>
<li>Operators and punctuation symbols</li>
<li>Comments (ignored)</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Syntax Analyzer</h2>

<p>
The <b>syntax analyzer</b> is implemented using <b>Java CUP</b>.  
It parses the token stream produced by the lexer and constructs an <b>Abstract Syntax Tree (AST)</b>.
</p>

<p>
The grammar specification is defined in:
</p>

<pre>spec/mjparser.cup</pre>

<p>
CUP generates the following classes:
</p>

<ul>
<li><b>MJParser.java</b> – LR parser implementation</li>
<li><b>sym.java</b> – terminal symbol definitions</li>
<li><b>AST classes</b> – generated syntax tree nodes</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Semantic Analysis</h2>

<p>
The semantic analyzer performs checks such as:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Symbol table management</li>
<li>Type compatibility checking</li>
<li>Validation of function calls and parameters</li>
<li>Control flow correctness (<code>break</code>, <code>continue</code>, <code>return</code>)</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Code Generation</h2>

<p>
After successful semantic analysis, the compiler generates bytecode for the 
<b>MicroJava virtual machine</b>.
</p>

<p>
The generated code is written to a <code>.obj</code> file which can be executed using the MicroJava runtime.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Building and Running the Compiler</h2>

<p>The project uses <b>Apache Ant</b> for building.</p>

<h3>Build</h3>

<pre>
ant build
</pre>

<p>
This command:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Generates lexer and parser code</li>
<li>Compiles the entire project</li>
</ul>

<h3>Running the compiler</h3>

<pre>
ant runObj
</pre>

<p>
This target:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Compiles the MicroJava source program</li>
<li>Generates the <code>.obj</code> file</li>
<li>Runs the program on the MicroJava virtual machine</li>
</ul>

